offers a generous sign-up bonus for new card members. Instead of having to spend a certain amount within the first few months of receiving the card, all you have to do is make any purchase within the first year of holding the card and you will be awarded 10,000 bonus miles and 10,000 Medallion® Qualification Miles. This will give you a good chunk of miles to use right away. Additionally, if you make $60,000 in purchases in a calendar year, you can earn up to 30,000 bonus miles and 30,000 Medallion® Qualification Miles.","This frequent flyer miles card will earn you one mile for every dollar you spend on all purchases and two miles for every dollar you spend on Delta purchases. For instance, if you use your card for Delta Air Line and Delta Vacation® purchases, you will earn the double miles.","You won’t have to worry about blackout dates when you go to redeem miles for travel, which is something we really like about this card. Additionally, this air miles card offers you access to Delta Sky Clubs, which feature a bunch of perks that will make sure you travel in style. When you use your card to purchase a Delta flight, you can check one bag for free. This card also offers a companion ticket once per year and 24/7 concierge service, which are both nice perks."]},"id":"7b81ba9b-bf61-4a26-a26e-d3f169aa19a6","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Key Features"},"id":"509e1ad5-1204-4c6b-a7a7-8e58ba24f44a","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["One of our favorite features of this air miles card is the miles you earn are not capped, nor do they expire. So you are free to rack up as many miles as you want without the fear that they will disappear if you don’t use them by a certain date. The Delta Reserve Credit Card also offers users a plethora of other key features and extras that are specifically beneficial to frequent travelers.","For instance, if you use your air miles card to purchase travel fare, you will automatically be covered with American Express’ travel accident insurance and baggage insurance plan. Additionally, if you use your card to rent a car, you will automatically be covered with its car rental loss and damage insurance.","This card also includes many shopping benefits. For example, if you use your card to purchase a product that comes with a manufacturer warranty, you will receive American Express’ extended product warranty, which will cover the product for an extra year. Additionally, this card includes purchase protection and return protection."]},"id":"faa5a335-5347-4bc6-ae8c-ca484439d04f","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"APR*"},"id":"cda23368-0c65-4090-928f-3a0b5a804f13","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["This American Express card doesn’t offer an introductory annual percentage rate, but we weren’t disappointed in its standard APR for purchases as it is already a fairly low spread. Any purchases you make with this air miles card will be held to a 15.24%-19.24% Variable APR if you carry a balance. You should plan on the same APR if you plan on using this card for balance transfer transactions. This card also includes a 25.24% Variable APR for cash advance transactions and a penalty APR of 27.24% Variable."]},"id":"9cca61c9-22c4-4aad-a1cc-a5139de69c38","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Fees &amp; Penalties"},"id":"87839465-b06e-48ff-8f42-3580a182a87e","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Other than its extremely high annual fee of $450, this air miles card features pretty standard fees. For instance, if you plan to use this credit card for any balance transfer or cash advance transactions, you can expect to see a $5 or 3% fee attached to every transaction. Additionally, for the frequent international traveler, when you use your card for purchases abroad, you will be charged a 2.7% fee for every transaction.","This card also features the industry standard late fee of up to $35, but as long as you pay your bill within the allotted 25-day grace period, you shouldn’t see that fee on your statement."]},"id":"c11